{
  "texts": [
    "They can modify their responses based on the user's needs, making the learning experience truly dynamic.",
    "For example, a learner struggling with a complex concept might receive a more detailed explanation, while another looking for a summary might receive a concise overview.",
    "This tailored approach to teaching and learning sets these conversational agents apart (Alaswad et al., 2023; González-Castro et al., 2021).Personalised learning is, at its heart, a recognition of the diversity of the student body (Li & Wong, 2021).",
    "No two learners share an identical academic journey.",
    "Each individual gains an educational experience informed by their past experiences, cultural background, cognitive strengths, and areas of challenge."
  ]
}